=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: =
1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-c=
olor: #ccc;">problem</a> here is that if you have someone ghostwrite all yo=
ur tweets and then you show up at board meetings and you=E2=80=99re boring,=
 word will get out, and your deal flow will dry up. (=E2=80=9CSure that guy=
 has good tweets but he=E2=80=99s on my board and he=E2=80=99s never either=
 given me good advice or told a good joke, don=E2=80=99t take his money,=E2=
=80=9D the founders will say to each other.) Another <a href=3D"https://lin=
k.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/29363474.276514/aHR0cHM6Ly90d2l0dGVyLmNv=
bS9tYXR0X2xldmluZS9zdGF0dXMvMTU4MDI3OTE1MTgzOTU2Nzg3Mw/607f07ceef4b8524a319=
a23cBb455852b" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_bl=
ank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; ba=
ckground-color: #ccc;">problem</a> is that, if you are a venture capitalist=
 and you are optimizing your Twitter brand, then your deal flow will over-i=
ndex on founders who spend too much time on Twitter. Which could be fine, w=
hy not, you might get to invest in the next Tesla or SpaceX. But it is poss=
ible that the people who are working to build the next generation of great =
businesses are hanging out on, you know, Hacker News, or TikTok, or possibl=
y even doing work instead of reading your jokes online.</p>
